WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.120 --> 00:00:04.400
The Barclays app

2
00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:08.240
How to go paperless and view your statements

3
00:00:09.200 --> 00:00:12.560
Did you know you can change your
statement preferences quickly and easily

4
00:00:12.560 --> 00:00:13.960
using the Barclays app?

5
00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:18.320
Start by tapping ‘More’ at the
bottom of the home screen.

6
00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:21.320
Next, tap on 'Manage accounts'

7
00:00:21.640 --> 00:00:24.520
then 'Statement and letter preferences'.

8
00:00:24.680 --> 00:00:26.680
Tap 'Go paperless'.

9
00:00:27.800 --> 00:00:32.400
See the benefits of going
paperless and tap 'Go paperless'.

10
00:00:32.400 --> 00:00:34.920
Read through the important information

11
00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:41.600
and if you're happy tap 'Confirm'
and your preferences will be saved.

12
00:00:41.960 --> 00:00:46.160
Tap 'Done' to return to the 'Statement
and letter’ preferences screen.

13
00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:47.720
Tap 'Close'

14
00:00:48.200 --> 00:00:51.760
then tap the back arrow
to return to the More menu.

15
00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:54.320
If you want to look at
one of your statements,

16
00:00:54.320 --> 00:00:57.440
tap on 'Statements and documents'.

17
00:00:57.440 --> 00:01:00.200
Select the statements
you want to look at.

18
00:01:00.840 --> 00:01:04.400
Now, to download or export
the statement on an iOS device,

19
00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:07.440
you will need to tap the arrow on the top right corner.

20
00:01:07.440 --> 00:01:12.920
Tap ‘Download’ and then choose where you
would like to store the statement on the device.

21
00:01:13.200 --> 00:01:16.680
To download or export the
statement on an Android device,

22
00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:19.280
tap the arrow on the top right corner.

23
00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:24.640
Tap ‘Download’ and then go to
the ‘Downloads’ folder to find the saved file.

24
00:01:24.640 --> 00:01:26.080
And there you go.

